Then what's the problem?

289
00:11:50,310 --> 00:11:51,110
Tell me.

290
00:11:52,110 --> 00:11:53,710
Can't I have my own troubles?

291
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:55,150
Can't I have

292
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:56,120
my own worries?

293
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:58,070
Si.

294
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:00,020
You're growing up,

295
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:01,500
having worries now.

296
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,240
Don't joke around with me like that!

297
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,640
I've always had worries.

298
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,010
Alright, tell me then.

299
00:12:14,110 --> 00:12:14,970
I'm listening.

300
00:12:19,150 --> 00:12:20,750
I've just suddenly realized

301
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:23,670
how useless I am.

302
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:27,710
I've been thinking about it a lot these past few days.

303
00:12:27,710 --> 00:12:28,750
Look at Hu.

304
00:12:28,950 --> 00:12:31,240
Since she was a kid, she's been told to study hard.

305
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:34,040
She aims to get into university, leave this place,

306
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,310
and later, go abroad with her older brother

307
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:36,910
for graduate school.

308
00:12:37,430 --> 00:12:38,280
Zhu Chao?

309
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,270
He's just waiting to take over his dad's job

310
00:12:40,270 --> 00:12:41,200
at the oil field.

311
00:12:41,830 --> 00:12:42,790
Qiang Xiaowa

312
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:45,910
wants to go to a teacher's college in Beijing,

313
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:47,110
because it's tuition-free,

314
00:12:47,110 --> 00:12:48,240
no dorm fees either.

315
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:50,990
After graduation, it's easy to find a job,

316
00:12:50,990 --> 00:12:53,050
and he can bring his grandpa with him.

317
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:54,270
Even Wei Xue says

318
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:55,630
she wants to go to Qingdao University

319
00:12:55,630 --> 00:12:56,830
to study accounting.

320
00:12:57,290 --> 00:12:59,290
And then there's me—no plans at all.

321
00:12:59,710 --> 00:13:00,710
I just think,

322
00:13:03,310 --> 00:13:04,110
wherever you go,

323
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:05,030
I'll go too.

324
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:07,650
Well, that's a plan, isn't it?

325
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:09,020
So,

326
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:12,430
where are you going?

327
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:21,560
I haven't figured it out.

328
00:13:23,590 --> 00:13:25,520
I just want to see what's out there.

329
00:13:28,870 --> 00:13:31,870
Seems like we're the only ones without any big dreams.

330
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:33,000
Why does there have to be

331
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,200
some concrete dream?

332
00:13:34,310 --> 00:13:36,070
People change

333
00:13:36,070 --> 00:13:37,130
as they grow older.

334
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,030
When I was little,

335
00:13:39,310 --> 00:13:40,840
I wanted to play the violin.

336
00:13:41,030 --> 00:13:43,720
In middle school, I wanted to perform

337
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,720
in the school anniversary play.

338
00:13:46,550 --> 00:13:48,990
In high school, I wanted to go to Hong Kong.

339
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,120
None of those things happened.

340
00:13:51,350 --> 00:13:53,210
Now, I'm rethinking everything.

341
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,530
We're different.

342
00:13:55,350 --> 00:13:57,110
Your dad doesn't look down on you.

343
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:57,630
Why do you think

344
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:58,390
my dad looks down on me?

345
00:13:58,390 --> 00:13:59,310
It's just because I have no ambition

346
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:00,190
and I'm not successful.

347
00:14:00,190 --> 00:14:02,260
What exactly does it mean to be successful?

348
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:04,590
Do you have to be a scientist,

349
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:05,710
a doctor, or a policeman

350
00:14:05,710 --> 00:14:07,150
to be considered successful?

351
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:08,750
If everyone in the world

352
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:09,940
did the same thing,

353
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:12,030
who would sweep the streets?

354
00:14:12,330 --> 00:14:13,270
Who would take out the trash?

355
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:15,390
Who would plant the trees, or work at the oil field?

356
00:14:15,390 --> 00:14:17,050
In our local farmers' market,

357
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:19,790
there are people buying and selling vegetables.

358
00:14:19,790 --> 00:14:20,990
Some want Someone wants popcorn?

359
00:14:20,990 --> 00:14:22,990
Well, there's someone who makes it.

360
00:14:24,010 --> 00:14:25,230
I can't even

361
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:27,310
make popcorn.

362
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:29,000
Then don't make popcorn.

363
00:14:29,950 --> 00:14:31,220
There are so many things in the world.

364
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:33,590
There's bound to be something that's right for the two of us.

365
00:14:33,590 --> 00:14:35,670
If we keep comparing ourselves to others,

366
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:36,790
how do we live?

367
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:39,230
I don't want to compare myself to others either,

368
00:14:39,230 --> 00:14:41,560
but life just seems to get worse by the day.

369
00:14:44,290 --> 00:14:46,090
I used to think our relationship

370
00:14:46,230 --> 00:14:47,620
was unshakable,

371
00:14:48,150 --> 00:14:49,490
but ever since Qiang Xiaowa came along,

372
00:14:49,490 --> 00:14:51,490
you spend all your time helping him.

373
00:14:51,890 --> 00:14:53,490
He's tall, handsome, smart,

374
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,850
and good at everything.

375
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:56,170
Compared to him,

376
00:14:56,170 --> 00:14:57,630
I feel like an idiot.

377
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,200
I used to think

378
00:14:59,230 --> 00:15:00,350
my family life was great

379
00:15:00,350 --> 00:15:01,820
and my parents were loving.

380
00:15:01,820 --> 00:15:02,590
But now?

381
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:05,240
My dad's first love came back,

382
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:07,170
and together they deceived my mom.

383
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:09,200
My dad's turned into a Chen Shimei.

384
00:15:10,350 --> 00:15:11,230
How did everything

385
00:15:11,230 --> 00:15:12,820
go wrong all of a sudden?

386
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:16,350
Even I feel like

387
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:18,750
I've become the worthless loser

388
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:20,080
my dad always said I was.

389
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:29,110
I didn't make it to Hong Kong,

390
00:15:30,710 --> 00:15:32,110
and I feel like a failure.

391
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:36,470
I didn't get selected as class monitor,

392
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:38,450
and I feel like a failure again.

393
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:41,490
I tried to help Qiang Xiaowa out of kindness,

394
00:15:41,490 --> 00:15:43,020
but he yelled at me instead.

395
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:44,710
It made me so angry.

396
00:15:45,430 --> 00:15:46,630
And look at Hua'er—

397
00:15:46,630 --> 00:15:47,630
after all the time

398
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:48,430
I spent trying to help,

399
00:15:48,430 --> 00:15:50,080
now, I have no idea

400
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:51,030
what she's doing

401
00:15:51,510 --> 00:15:52,670
or where she is.

402
00:15:53,710 --> 00:15:55,350
Since high school,

403
00:15:55,590 --> 00:15:57,630
I haven't been able to keep up with my studies.

404
00:15:57,630 --> 00:15:58,680
At one point, I even wondered

405
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,510
if I ate something

406
00:15:59,510 --> 00:16:00,820
that ruined my brain.

407
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,790
Cheng Yaya keeps getting better,

408
00:16:02,790 --> 00:16:04,590
which just makes me look dumber.

409
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:06,960
And I feel like my mom

410
00:16:06,990 --> 00:16:08,110
is biased towards Cheng Yaya,

411
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:09,440
which really annoys me.

412
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:12,510
My parents were getting divorced,

413
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:14,140
and I sided with my dad,

414
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:15,390
telling him not to be afraid,

415
00:16:15,390 --> 00:16:16,150
that I'd stand with him.

416
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:18,190
But then my dad switched sides at the last minute,

417
00:16:18,190 --> 00:16:20,720
and now I'm the biggest traitor in the family.

418
00:16:23,310 --> 00:16:24,750
Tell me, is there a single thing

419
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,580
in my life that's not a mess?

420
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:28,990
The other day, my mom asked me,

421
00:16:28,990 --> 00:16:30,670
"What are you running around

422
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:31,930
doing every day?

423
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:34,750
What have you actually accomplished?"

424
00:16:35,460 --> 00:16:37,210
And when I thought about it,

425
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:41,990
I realized—I haven't accomplished anything.

426
00:16:42,490 --> 00:16:44,890
It seems like the two of us have it the worst.

427
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:45,910
But

428
00:16:45,990 --> 00:16:47,630
you know

429
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:49,030
how I figured things out?

430
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:54,380
It's because I saw Yuan Shanqing,

431
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:56,190
I saw Qiang Xiaowa,

432
00:16:56,190 --> 00:16:57,470
and I saw Hua'er.

433
00:16:57,900 --> 00:16:59,210
I realized that they are

434
00:16:59,210 --> 00:17:01,010
the ones truly living in misery,

435
00:17:01,590 --> 00:17:04,130
but they haven't given up,

436
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,730
and they never complained.

437
00:17:07,270 --> 00:17:08,400
And then there's Hu.

438
00:17:09,190 --> 00:17:11,020
The three of us grew up together,

439
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:13,230
but do we really understand her?

440
00:17:13,510 --> 00:17:14,750
Other than that one time

441
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:16,530
when she tried to drown herself,

442
00:17:16,530 --> 00:17:18,990
she never talked about her struggles again.

443
00:17:18,990 --> 00:17:20,579
After that incident,

444
00:17:21,630 --> 00:17:22,630
I kept wondering,

445
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:25,770
how has Hu managed to live

446
00:17:26,390 --> 00:17:27,619
all these years?

447
00:17:34,090 --> 00:17:34,850
Si,

448
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:35,950
you know why

449
00:17:35,950 --> 00:17:37,790
we have no ambition,

450
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,950
and why we're the ones with no goals?

451
00:17:39,950 --> 00:17:40,750
Why?

452
00:17:41,430 --> 00:17:43,430
Because we're the luckiest ones.

453
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:45,250
The universe has given us

454
00:17:45,270 --> 00:17:46,420
the best lives.

455
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,020
So,

456
00:17:50,450 --> 00:17:51,450
we can't waste

457
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:53,000
this amazing opportunity.

458
00:17:54,110 --> 00:17:56,110
Think about it—our group.

459
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,510
You're the big brother, I'm the big sister.

460
00:17:58,510 --> 00:18:00,840
We're the backbone, the soul of the group.

461
00:18:01,390 --> 00:18:02,390
It's not just our little group—

462
00:18:02,390 --> 00:18:03,990
isn't Linqi No. 2 High School

463
00:18:04,070 --> 00:18:05,470
also centered around us?

464
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:08,350
So, when it comes to studying,

465
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:09,880
let's give it our best shot.

466
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:12,400
Whatever we get into, we get into.

467
00:18:13,470 --> 00:18:14,550
As for dreams,

468
00:18:15,630 --> 00:18:16,560
what's the rush?

469
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,640
We can take our time to figure them out.

470
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:20,440
We've got a long life ahead of us.

471
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:23,740
Yeah,

472
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:25,910
we've got a long life ahead of us.

473
00:18:26,460 --> 00:18:27,690
No dreams? So what.

474
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:28,760
Exactly. Like I'm gonna

475
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:30,710
look down on you for not being successful?

476
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:32,240
Who's looking down on whom?

477
00:18:32,390 --> 00:18:33,460
Let me tell you something,

478
00:18:33,460 --> 00:18:35,430
don't just casually come over to my house from now on.

479
00:18:35,430 --> 00:18:36,090
Why not?

480
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,550
You don't want me to see that big digger of yours?

481
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:38,720
Excavator. It's an excavator!

482
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:39,540
My mom bought it for me

483
00:18:39,540 --> 00:18:40,430
and insisted I wear it.

484
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:41,510
It wasn't my choice.

485
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:43,270
An excavator, huh?

486
00:18:43,270 --> 00:18:43,880
Let me see.

487
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:45,150
What are you doing?

488
00:18:45,150 --> 00:18:46,230
Are you a pervert?

489
00:18:46,260 --> 00:18:47,190
Cheng Miaomiao!

490
00:18:47,420 --> 00:18:48,390
Cheng Miaomiao!

491
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:55,790
Alright, in a few days,

492
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:57,110
you can go buy the train tickets.

493
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:58,370
We'll all go together.

494
00:18:59,270 --> 00:19:01,630
Old friends, out on a trip.

495
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:02,990
That sounds great!

496
00:19:03,390 --> 00:19:04,390
Grandma!

497
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,160
-Miaomiao.
-What brings you here?

498
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:07,920
You didn't tell me!

499
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,950
I've missed you so much!

500
00:19:08,950 --> 00:19:10,070
I've missed you too!

501
00:19:10,070 --> 00:19:10,830
But if you missed me so much,

502
00:19:10,830 --> 00:19:12,090
why didn't you call me?

503
00:19:12,450 --> 00:19:14,310
You're the most lively one in the family!

504
00:19:14,310 --> 00:19:15,310
Look at my dad, he's already got gray hair,

505
00:19:15,310 --> 00:19:16,770
but you don't have any yet.

506
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:17,780
Grandma!

507
00:19:18,460 --> 00:19:19,940
-Yaya.
-I miss you so much!

508
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,270
I've missed you too!

509
00:19:21,710 --> 00:19:22,740
When did you get here?

510
00:19:22,740 --> 00:19:24,110
I would've picked you up if I'd known!

511
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:25,070
I wanted to surprise you.

512
00:19:25,070 --> 00:19:26,890
But turns out neither of you was home.

513
00:19:26,890 --> 00:19:28,820
I was just out for a walk with Uncle.

514
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:30,030
Mom.

515
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:31,390
I've missed you so much!

516
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:32,350
So annoying. Get lost.

517
00:19:32,350 --> 00:19:33,810
I don't have a son like you.

518
00:19:33,830 --> 00:19:35,670
Mom, why are you talking like that?

519
00:19:35,670 --> 00:19:36,990
I was just telling my sister the other day.

520
00:19:36,990 --> 00:19:37,950
We should pick you up and bring you over.

521
00:19:37,950 --> 00:19:39,030
How could we celebrate the new year

522
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:40,510
without you? Isn't that right?

523
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:41,590
Well, now that I see you,

524
00:19:41,590 --> 00:19:43,190
it's going to be hard to enjoy this New Year.

525
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:43,870
And it's getting hard for me

526
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:45,110
to get through my days.

527
00:19:45,110 --> 00:19:47,030
Mom, after New Year, please send him away.

528
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:48,070
I can't leave yet.

529
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:49,490
I've still got big things to handle.

530
00:19:49,490 --> 00:19:51,420
What now? Owe someone money again?

531
00:19:51,470 --> 00:19:53,310
That was a one-time thing, alright?

532
00:19:53,310 --> 00:19:55,110
Stop bringing it up over and over.

533
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:56,860
So, who's the new person you're after?

534
00:19:56,860 --> 00:19:57,950
Exactly!

535
00:19:57,970 --> 00:19:59,030
First, he had his eye on our English teacher,

536
00:19:59,030 --> 00:19:59,830
Then on our director.

537
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:00,990
Typical of him.

538
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:02,190
Nonsense, nonsense!

539
00:20:02,430 --> 00:20:03,310
Grandma, I can testify.

540
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:04,510
Everything my sister said is absolutely true.

541
00:20:04,510 --> 00:20:05,230
-You two...
-I knew it.

542
00:20:05,230 --> 00:20:06,310
Let me tell you.

543
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:07,510
Make sure to tell that teacher

544
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:09,270
to stay away from this troublemaker.

545
00:20:09,270 --> 00:20:09,790
Mom, am I still

546
00:20:09,790 --> 00:20:10,590
your dear son or not?

547
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:11,910
Can you support me just once?

548
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:13,630
Can I support bad people doing bad things?

549
00:20:13,630 --> 00:20:16,160
Supporting that would make me an accomplice!

550
00:20:16,990 --> 00:20:17,630
Mom. Did you come by yourself?

551
00:20:17,630 --> 00:20:19,070
What about Dad?

552
00:20:19,090 --> 00:20:20,150
Don't mention him.

553
00:20:20,660 --> 00:20:21,960
What do you want to eat tonight?

554
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:22,980
Coke chicken wings.

555
00:20:22,980 --> 00:20:24,510
-Chicken wings?
-Cola chicken wings.

556
00:20:24,510 --> 00:20:27,140
Here, this one's for Miaomiao,

557
00:20:27,940 --> 00:20:29,790
And this one's for Yaya.

558
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:31,030
Thanks, Grandma!

559
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:33,150
I've adored you two since you were little.

560
00:20:33,150 --> 00:20:35,100
Such lovable kids.

561
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,750
Our Miaomiao—

562
00:20:36,780 --> 00:20:38,230
she's pretty, kind-hearted,

563
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:39,760
and she's smart too.

564
00:20:40,590 --> 00:20:42,590
Just looking at her makes you happy!

565
00:20:42,630 --> 00:20:44,070
And Yaya

566
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:45,910
isn't just anyone either—

567
00:20:46,190 --> 00:20:47,550
he's smart

568
00:20:47,590 --> 00:20:48,670
and capable,

569
00:20:49,590 --> 00:20:51,230
and he can handle anything.

